quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  70,36,"What is with those who disbelieve, stretching their necks towards you"
  70,37,"From the right, and from the left, banding together"
  70,38,Is every one of them aspiring to be admitted into a Garden of Bliss
  70,39,No indeed! We created them from what they know
  70,40,"I swear by the Lord of the Easts and the Wests, that We are Able"
  70,41,"To replace them with better than they, and We are not to be outdone"
  70,42,"So leave them to blunder and play, until they meet their Day which they are promised"
  70,43,"The Day when they will emerge from the tombs in a rush, as though they were hurrying towards a target"
  70,44,Their eyes cast down; overwhelmed by humiliation. This is the Day which they were promised